11/03/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Paddy Ashdown said in an interview published Monday (10 March) in the Sarajevo daily <I>Dnevni Avaz</I> that the international community in BiH has new methods for dealing with war crimes suspects who are still at large.
Ashdown said the new instruments go beyond freezing financial assets, adding that the international community is determined to break the network supporting indictees sought by the UN war crimes tribunal.
(FoNet - 11/03/03;
RTRS - 10/03/03)
